---
export const prerender = true;

import Main from '../layouts/main.astro';
import ResumeEntry from '../components/resume-entry.astro';
---

<Main title='About' description='A little bit more about me' slug='/about/'>
  <strong class='text-sm text-brand-muted'>About</strong>
  <h1 id='about-me' class='mb-0'>
    <a href='/about/#about-me'>More about me</a>
  </h1>
  <p>Hey there! 👋</p>
  <p>
    I'm Paul — a developer, technical product marketer and content engineer. Since 2005 I've moved
    from design and advertising into engineering, developer advocacy and, most recently, product marketing. Today I help
    developer-focused companies explain what they've built and why it matters.
  </p>

  <h2 id='experience'>
    <a href='/about/#experience'>Experience</a>
  </h2>

  <ResumeEntry company='Mastra' title='Technical Product Marketing Manager' dates='May 2025 – Present'>
    Started on the documentation team for
    <a href='https://mastra.ai/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Mastra</a>, an open-source TypeScript framework for
    building AI agents, then moved into product marketing — planning and running launches, creating technical content
    and managing social media, all in close collaboration with the engineering team and feeding insights back into the
    docs.
  </ResumeEntry>

  <ResumeEntry company='Neon' title='Technical Product Marketing Manager' dates='Jan 2025 – May 2025'>
    Planned and shipped product launches, built the
    <a href='https://neon.tech/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Neon</a> Twin local-development workflow for enterprise
    customers, and wrote technical guides and fast-turnaround, AI-focused thought leadership.
  </ResumeEntry>

  <ResumeEntry company='Freelance' title='Independent Advocate' dates='Oct 2023 – Jan 2025'>
    Built, demoed and wrote about tools across the stack, designed and delivered product-marketing campaigns, served on
    <a href='https://www.smashingmagazine.com/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Smashing Magazine</a>'s panel of experts
    and guest-authored for <a href='https://thenewstack.io/author/paulscanlon/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
      >The New Stack</a
    >, while traveling the world ✈️.
  </ResumeEntry>

  <ResumeEntry company='Neon' title='Developer Advocate' dates='Aug 2023 – Oct 2023'>
    Built demos and technical content focused on Postgres for JavaScript engineers, drove sign-ups through advocacy, and
    developed an external publishing strategy to expand reach within the JavaScript ecosystem.
  </ResumeEntry>

  <ResumeEntry company='Cockroach Labs' title='Technical Evangelist' dates='Nov 2022 – Jul 2023'>
    Created content and demos to showcase new
    <a href='https://www.cockroachlabs.com/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>CockroachDB</a> features for product
    launches, pairing digital storytelling with deep technical knowledge of distributed SQL to communicate product value
    to technical audiences.
  </ResumeEntry>

  <ResumeEntry company='Gatsby' title='Senior Software Engineer / Developer Relations' dates='Oct 2021 – Oct 2022'>
    Acted as <a href='https://www.gatsbyjs.com/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Gatsby</a>'s sole developer advocate —
    engaging the community across Slack, Discord and GitHub, and building developer-focused demos, blog posts, tutorials
    and livestreams across the marketing, product and growth teams. (Previously Technical Content Writer, 2020–2021.)
  </ResumeEntry>

  <h2 id='writing'>
    <a href='/about/#writing'>Writing</a>
  </h2>

  <p>
    From 2020 onwards I've been increasingly focused on technical writing, with articles published in
    <a href='https://www.smashingmagazine.com/author/paul-scanlon/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>Smashing Magazine</a>,
    <a href='https://css-tricks.com/roll-your-own-comments-with-gatsby-and-faunadb/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'
      >CSS-Tricks</a
    >
    and <a href='https://thenewstack.io/author/paulscanlon/' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>The New Stack</a>, as well as
    on the blogs of the companies I've worked at. The full archive lives at
    <a href='/articles/'>paulie.dev/articles</a>, and I'm fairly active in open source over on
    <a href='https://github.com/PaulieScanlon' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>GitHub</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id='before-tech'>
    <a href='/about/#before-tech'>Before tech</a>
  </h2>

  <p>
    A long time ago I was a designer, but after a few years of pixel-pushing I realised code was just better. I spent
    years in advertising designing and building interactive campaigns — first in Flash, later HTML, JavaScript and CSS —
    and picked up a few awards, including a
    <a
      href='https://www.dandad.org/awards/professional/2010/graphic-design/17943/one-in-seven/'
      target='_blank'
      rel='noopener'>D&amp;AD</a
    > and a <b>BAFTA</b>.
  </p>

  <p>
    In 2012 I co-founded <strong>super natural</strong>, a London digital production studio, and grew it from my kitchen
    table to a team of ten, working with brands like Channel 4, ITV and Netflix. In 2016, with JavaScript frameworks on
    the rise, I took the leap into React and never looked back.
  </p>

  <h2 id='education'>
    <a href='/about/#education'>Education</a>
  </h2>

  <ResumeEntry company='Leeds Beckett University' title='BSc Multimedia Technology · 1st Class with Honours' />
  <ResumeEntry company='University of Brighton' title='HND Multimedia Technology · Distinction' />
</Main>
